The paper deals with the complexity of approximating the matching polynomial on graphs, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory, graph theory, and algebraic geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
